  34. (* The sign of initial_size encodes the fact that a traversal is
  35.    ongoing or not.

  37.    This disables the efficient in place implementation of resizing.

  96. let copy_bucketlist = function
  97.   | Empty -> Empty
  98.   | Cons {key; data; next} ->
  99.       let rec loop prec = function
  100.         | Empty -> ()
  101.         | Cons {key; data; next} ->
  102.             let r = Cons {key; data; next} in
  103.             begin match prec with
  104.             | Empty -> assert false
  105.             | Cons prec ->  prec.next <- r
  106.             end;
  107.             loop r next
  108.       in
  109.       let r = Cons {key; data; next} in
  110.       loop r next;
  111.       r

  113. ‌let copy h = { h with data = Array.map copy_bucketlist h.data }

  117. ‌let insert_all_buckets indexfun inplace odata ndata =
  118.   let nsize = Array.length ndata in
  119.   let ndata_tail = Array.make nsize Empty in
  120.   let rec insert_bucket = function
  121.     | Empty -> ()
  122.     | Cons {key; data; next} as cell ->
  123.         let cell =
  124.           if inplace then cell
  125.           else Cons {key; data; next = Empty}
  126.         in
  127.         let nidx = indexfun key in
  128.         begin match ndata_tail.(nidx) with
  129.         | Empty -> ndata.(nidx) <- cell;
  130.         | Cons tail -> tail.next <- cell;
  131.         end;
  132.         ndata_tail.(nidx) <- cell;
  133.         insert_bucket next
  134.   in
  135.   for i = 0 to Array.length odata - 1 do
  136.     insert_bucket odata.(i)
  137.   done;
  138.   if inplace then
  139.     for i = 0 to nsize - 1 do
  140.       match ndata_tail.(i) with
  141.       | Empty -> ()
  142.       | Cons tail -> tail.next <- Empty
  143.     done

  145. ‌let resize indexfun h =
  146.   let odata = h.data in
  147.   let osize = Array.length odata in
  148.   let nsize = osize * 2 in
  149.   if nsize < Sys.max_array_length then begin
  150.     let ndata = Array.make nsize Empty in
  151.     let inplace = not (ongoing_traversal h) in
  152.     h.data <- ndata;          (* so that indexfun sees the new bucket count *)

  154.   end

  156. let iter f h =
  157.   let rec do_bucket = function
  158.     | Empty ->
  159.         ()
  160.     | Cons{key; data; next} ->
  161.         f key data; do_bucket next in
  162.   let old_trav = ongoing_traversal h in
  163.   if not old_trav then flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  164.   try
  165.     let d = h.data in
  166.     for i = 0 to Array.length d - 1 do
  167.       do_bucket d.(i)
  168.     done;
  169.     if not old_trav then flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  170.   with exn when not old_trav ->
  171.     flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  172.     raise exn

  174. ‌let rec filter_map_inplace_bucket f h i prec = function
  175.   | Empty ->
  176.       begin match prec with
  177.       | Empty -> h.data.(i) <- Empty
  178.       | Cons c -> c.next <- Empty
  179.       end
  180.   | (Cons ({key; data; next} as c)) as slot ->
  181.       begin match f key data with
  182.       | None ->
  183.           h.size <- h.size - 1;
  184.           filter_map_inplace_bucket f h i prec next
  185.       | Some data ->
  186.           begin match prec with
  187.           | Empty -> h.data.(i) <- slot
  188.           | Cons c -> c.next <- slot
  189.           end;
  190.           c.data <- data;
  191.           filter_map_inplace_bucket f h i slot next
  192.       end

  194. let filter_map_inplace f h =
  195.   let d = h.data in
  196.   let old_trav = ongoing_traversal h in
  197.   if not old_trav then flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  198.   try
  199.     for i = 0 to Array.length d - 1 do
  200.       filter_map_inplace_bucket f h i Empty h.data.(i)
  201.     done;
  202.     if not old_trav then flip_ongoing_traversal h
  203.   with exn when not old_trav ->
  204.     flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  205.     raise exn

  207. ‌let fold f h init =
  208.   let rec do_bucket b accu =
  209.     match b with
  210.       Empty ->
  211.         accu
  212.     | Cons{key; data; next} ->
  213.         do_bucket next (f key data accu) in
  214.   let old_trav = ongoing_traversal h in
  215.   if not old_trav then flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  216.   try
  217.     let d = h.data in
  218.     let accu = ref init in
  219.     for i = 0 to Array.length d - 1 do
  220.       accu := do_bucket d.(i) !accu
  221.     done;
  222.     if not old_trav then flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  223.     !accu
  224.   with exn when not old_trav ->
  225.     flip_ongoing_traversal h;
  226.     raise exn

  239. ‌let stats h =
  240.   let mbl =
  241.     Array.fold_left (fun m b -> Int.max m (bucket_length 0 b)) 0 h.data in
  242.   let histo = Array.make (mbl + 1) 0 in
  243.   Array.iter
  244.     (fun b ->
  245.       let l = bucket_length 0 b in
  246.       histo.(l) <- histo.(l) + 1)
  247.     h.data;
  248.   { num_bindings = h.size;
  249.     num_buckets = Array.length h.data;
  250.     max_bucket_length = mbl;
  251.     bucket_histogram = histo }

  255. let to_seq tbl =
  256.   (* capture current array, so that even if the table is resized we
  257.      keep iterating on the same array *)
  258.   let tbl_data = tbl.data in
  259.   (* state: index * next bucket to traverse *)
  260. ‌  let rec aux i buck () = match buck with
  261.     | Empty ->
  262.         if i = Array.length tbl_data
  263.         then Seq.Nil
  264.         else aux(i+1) tbl_data.(i) ()
  265.     | Cons {key; data; next} ->
  266.         Seq.Cons ((key, data), aux i next)
  267.   in
  268.   aux 0 Empty

  270. ‌let to_seq_keys m = Seq.map fst (to_seq m)

  272. ‌let to_seq_values m = Seq.map snd (to_seq m)

  356. ‌    let key_index h key =
  357.       (H.seeded_hash h.seed key) land (Array.length h.data - 1)

  359. ‌    let add h key data =
  360.       let i = key_index h key in
  361.       let bucket = Cons{key; data; next=h.data.(i)} in
  362.       h.data.(i) <- bucket;
  363.       h.size <- h.size + 1;
  364.       if h.size > Array.length h.data lsl 1 then resize key_index h

  366. ‌    let rec remove_bucket h i key prec = function
  367.       | Empty ->
  368.           ()
  369.       | (Cons {key=k; next}) as c ->
  370.           if H.equal k key
  371.           then begin
  372.             h.size <- h.size - 1;
  373.             match prec with
  374.             | Empty -> h.data.(i) <- next
  375.             | Cons c -> c.next <- next
  376.           end
  377.           else remove_bucket h i key c next

  379. ‌    let remove h key =
  380.       let i = key_index h key in
  381.       remove_bucket h i key Empty h.data.(i)

  383. ‌    let rec find_rec key = function
  384.       | Empty ->
  385.           raise Not_found
  386.       | Cons{key=k; data; next} ->
  387.           if H.equal key k then data else find_rec key next

  389. ‌    let find h key =
  390.       match h.data.(key_index h key) with
  391.       | Empty -> raise Not_found
  392.       | Cons{key=k1; data=d1; next=next1} ->
  393.           if H.equal key k1 then d1 else
  394.           match next1 with
  395.           | Empty -> raise Not_found
  396.           | Cons{key=k2; data=d2; next=next2} ->
  397.               if H.equal key k2 then d2 else
  398.               match next2 with
  399.               | Empty -> raise Not_found
  400.               | Cons{key=k3; data=d3; next=next3} ->
  401.                   if H.equal key k3 then d3 else find_rec key next3

  403. ‌    let rec find_rec_opt key = function
  404.       | Empty ->
  405.           None
  406.       | Cons{key=k; data; next} ->
  407.           if H.equal key k then Some data else find_rec_opt key next

  409. ‌    let find_opt h key =
  410.       match h.data.(key_index h key) with
  411.       | Empty -> None
  412.       | Cons{key=k1; data=d1; next=next1} ->
  413.           if H.equal key k1 then Some d1 else
  414.           match next1 with
  415.           | Empty -> None
  416.           | Cons{key=k2; data=d2; next=next2} ->
  417.               if H.equal key k2 then Some d2 else
  418.               match next2 with
  419.               | Empty -> None
  420.               | Cons{key=k3; data=d3; next=next3} ->
  421.                   if H.equal key k3 then Some d3 else find_rec_opt key next3

  423. ‌    let find_all h key =
  424.       let[@tail_mod_cons] rec find_in_bucket = function
  425.       | Empty ->
  426.           []
  427.       | Cons{key=k; data=d; next} ->
  428.           if H.equal k key
  429.           then d :: find_in_bucket next
  430.           else find_in_bucket next in
  431.       find_in_bucket h.data.(key_index h key)

  433. ‌    let rec replace_bucket key data = function
  434.       | Empty ->
  435.           true
  436.       | Cons ({key=k; next} as slot) ->
  437.           if H.equal k key
  438.           then (slot.key <- key; slot.data <- data; false)
  439.           else replace_bucket key data next

  441. ‌    let replace h key data =
  442.       let i = key_index h key in
  443.       let l = h.data.(i) in
  444.       if replace_bucket key data l then begin
  445.         h.data.(i) <- Cons{key; data; next=l};
  446.         h.size <- h.size + 1;
  447.         if h.size > Array.length h.data lsl 1 then resize key_index h
  448.       end

  450. ‌    let rec mem_in_bucket key = function
  451.       | Empty ->
  452.           false
  453.       | Cons{key=k; next} ->
  454.           H.equal k key || mem_in_bucket key next

  456. ‌    let mem h key =
  457.       mem_in_bucket key h.data.(key_index h key)

  459. ‌    let add_seq tbl i =
  460.       Seq.iter (fun (k,v) -> add tbl k v) i

  462.     let replace_seq tbl i =
  463.       Seq.iter (fun (k,v) -> replace tbl k v) i

  465.     let of_seq i =
  466.       let tbl = create 16 in
  467.       replace_seq tbl i;
  468.       tbl
